title: [Serious] I just realized that the only reason I'm going to college is because my parents want me to
self_text: Hey, so I’m a high school senior and I’ve been getting into colleges but I’m realizing that I don’t actually *want* to go to college. My parents are pressuring me really hard (especially my mom) and have always pushed me to aim for university. They think it’s what I need to be successful in life. I haven’t told them yet because I know they will freak out and I’m scared of disappointing them. But when I imagine myself attending classes/doing work, I feel… empty. Like it’s not what I want at all.
